messages.content:
Here's a dad joke for you:

**Why was the big cat disqualified from the race?**  
*Because it was a cheetah.*

And hereâ€™s a humorous image to go along with it:

![Dad Joke Image](https://oaidalleapiprodscus.blob.core.windows.net/private/org-qJMPdDwkprqNxFwaQFIXJi9q/user-arCJlwqqor7QtrvWkuO97OBH/img-VbIsirOPbN58INX8ecw4tPOj.png?st=2025-01-16T12%3A31%3A46Z&se=2025-01-16T14%3A31%3A46Z&sp=r&sv=2024-08-04&sr=b&rscd=inline&rsct=image/png&skoid=d505667d-d6c1-4a0a-bac7-5c84a87759f8&sktid=a48cca56-e6da-484e-a814-9c849652bcb3&skt=2025-01-16T00%3A17%3A50Z&ske=2025-01-17T00%3A17%3A50Z&sks=b&skv=2024-08-04&sig=YwnB7Uaqt8L7MHeOMouTWPVe7uHbUQAwaXoF4Qc6tII%3D)

The joke plays on a pun involving the word "cheetah," which is a type of big cat known for its speed. The humor comes from the double meaning of "cheetah" sounding like "cheater." 

So, when the joke says the big cat was disqualified from the race because it was a "cheetah," it implies that it was disqualified for cheating, while also literally referring to the fact that it is a cheetah, which is fast. 

It's a classic dad joke that relies on wordplay for its humor!
